110
00:09:35,529 --> 00:09:38,559
Dr. Li, can you tell us something about

111
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:42,440
this visitor codenamed F in the statement?

112
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:44,900
He

113
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:48,200
is the smartest and

114
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
the purest person I have ever seen.

115
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:55,169
Do you know according to the ethics code of Chinese Psychological Society,

116
00:09:55,169 --> 00:09:58,370
psychological counselors are not allowed to have an intimate relationship with their visitors

117
00:09:58,370 --> 00:10:01,510
within three years as of the end of their counseling sessions?

118
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:03,269
I know.

119
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:07,090
Do you think your behavior is not professional?

120
00:10:07,090 --> 00:10:10,960
Do you have anything to explain regarding this matter?

121
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:15,130
I don't regret what happened at all.

122
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:24,540
It's all my fault and I am willing to bear all the consequences.

123
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:30,180
Actually, it's normal to have positive transference and negative transference

124
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:32,330
between psychological counselors and their visitors.

125
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:36,769
How to handle the visitors' strong erotic transference without hurting their feelings

126
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:42,419
and even use it as an opportunity to treat them will reflect the expertise of a psychological counselor.

127
00:10:42,419 --> 00:10:46,909
For example, a person who always tries to please everyone.

128
00:10:46,909 --> 00:10:50,660
Only when he or she shows the same tendency towards the counselor,

129
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:55,139
can the counselor find his or her weakness in the visitor's interpersonal relationship?

130
00:10:55,139 --> 00:11:01,680
On the opposite, if this counselor finds it boring when the visitor keeps talking,

131
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:07,799
the negative feelings will also remind them that this visitor might also bore people in his or her life.

132
00:11:07,799 --> 00:11:09,520
That's right.

133
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:16,099
The visitors will unconsciously project their important emotions onto the counselor

134
00:11:16,099 --> 00:11:18,570
which will help the counselor better understand this visitor.

135
00:11:18,570 --> 00:11:21,470
The feelings the counselor has towards the visitor

136
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:26,030
can also help them understand the visitor's unspoken problems.

137
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,689
I don't think it's difficult

138
00:11:27,689 --> 00:11:30,490
for Li Yun who is a professional to deal with negative transference well.

139
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:31,790
So how could this happen?

140
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:34,760
Li Yun was a very talented student of mine.

141
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:37,880
The mistake she made will ruin her career

142
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:41,450
which will bring a huge loss to our discipline.

143
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:45,669
Professor. Will she be revoked her practicing license as a counselor?

144
00:11:45,669 --> 00:11:49,669
I don't know the result yet. But I've done everything I can.

145
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:55,349
But I heard that she is going abroad next month. I think it's good for her.

146
00:11:55,349 --> 00:11:59,169
Everyone will have the time to calm down when she's away.

147
00:11:59,169 --> 00:12:01,690
Aren't you curious?

148
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:02,960
